- The integer matrix parameter `grid` must not be null.
- The integer result is the maximum number of cherries collected by both robots following the specified rules.
- Both robots start at the top row of the grid, with Robot #1 at the top-left corner and Robot #2 at the top-right corner.
- Robots can move to the next row by going down and either left, straight, or right.
- When a robot passes through a cell, it collects all cherries in that cell, and the cell becomes empty.
- If both robots reach the same cell, only one robot can collect the cherries.
- Both robots must reach the bottom row of the grid.
- The grid dimensions must be between 2x2 and 70x70.
- The values in the grid must be between 0 and 100.